result.execSummary:
The defendant Caitlin Kelly Maloney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While Revoked (Misdemeanor)], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: $50 fine plus costs. 60 days to pay fine/costs to avoid serving 10 days jail time.

10 days stayed. If defendant pays fine and costs in full on or before 10/31/15, stay will be permanent. If defendant fails to pay fine and costs in full on or before 10/31/15, stay will be lifted and defendant will need to report to jail to serve the remaining 10 days. Consecutive to 15-CT-31. Good time and huber privileges granted. Credit for time served.  Sentence can be served in Brown County. Defendant is responsible for notifying the Door County Jail if sentence is being served in a different county.  60 days from sentencing date to report.
